<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-179-859  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 179 859.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DG Review  July 1990 v11 n1 p12(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The three Cs. (automated change control and configurationmanagement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Nix, Kevin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Automating the process of change control and configurationmanagement eliminates the problem of controlling and trackingchanges to all software components and the difficulty in managingthe interrelationships between changes.andP;  Change control recordsand tracks changes to components of an application.andP;  Configurationmanagement supplies a definition of the change cycle, releasecycle, and functional responsibilities.andP;  Configuration managementprovides a way to organize, manage, and track all components as aunit.andP;  When the process is automated, a single control area isdefined to store all the product's components.andP;  Tools areavailable to automate the change control and configurationmanagement process.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Control SystemsSoftware DesignApplications ProgrammingProduct Life CycleAutomationConfiguration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>